<p><strong>Time, Day One</strong></p>
<p>Illustrator Tim O’Brien has painted more Time covers in the past 30 years than any other artist. Best known for his series of four paintings for the magazine depicting former President Donald Trump in the midst of a growing storm in the Oval Office, the illustrator decided to continue with the theme by examining the mess that new President Joe Biden inherited from his predecessor.</p>
<p>In the powerful image, Biden is pensively looking out of a trashed Oval Office window, which appears to be surrounded by flames. Meanwhile, graffiti is scrawled on a curtain and the Resolute Desk, and one of Trump’s signature Make America Great Again caps is fittingly strewn among a pile of rubbish on the floor.</p>
