<p><strong>Rubbish Famzine, No.10</strong></p>
<p>Produced by the Singapore-based Lim family and inspired by a family trip to Tokyo, Rubbish Famzine has recorded their lives together for the best part of a decade. The tenth issue of the publication was supposed to involve a return to Tokyo but with the pandemic having other ideas, the family decided to bring the Japanese capital to their home instead.</p>
<p>The cover of the brilliantly OTT issue came wrapped together with a series of miniature reproductions of items the family brought back from their trip to Japan, including a Rubbish-branded Casio digital watch which is used to seal the magazine closed. Because, why not?</p>
