<p><strong>Dazed &amp; Confused, Back to Life</strong></p>
<p>As we slowly emerged from lockdown fatigue, Dazed’s summer issue marked the historic NHS vaccine drive as it reached younger parts of the UK population. ⁠⁠The first issue from the publication’s recently instated editor-in-chief Ib Kamara, cover photographer Paolo Roversi used a vaccination shoot concept as a jumping off point to envisage a whole new world.</p>
<p>“We were talking about this issue as a ‘National Geographic for global youth culture’ and what that could mean,” says Kamara. “It just had to start with the pandemic and the vaccine – a global problem and a global solution. How do we create around this? It’s this ‘somehow’ – the idea that, against all odds culture will find a way – that makes 2021 such an inspiring and historic year.”</p>
