<p><strong>Vogue Italia, The Do It Yourself Issue</strong></p>
<p>A Rihanna mag cover is always guaranteed to make a splash, but the team at Vogue Italia took things one step further when they asked her to take the reins for its Do It Yourself issue. Operating as stylist, muse, project director and photographer, the cover sees the artist adorned in a tantalising Valentino dress and thigh-high lace-up heels. Meanwhile, creative director Ferdinando Verderi’s whimsical collage amalgamation of paper clips, twigs, plant stems and thread overlaid on top became the perfect tribute to the art of DIY.</p>
