r 2021 20"></div>
<p><strong>The New York Times Magazine, The Puzzle of Asian American Identity</strong></p>
<p>It wouldn’t be a best mag covers round up without a nod to the stellar work of the design team at the New York Times Magazine, and this year is no exception. One of the publication’s most impactful covers of the year addressed the puzzle of Asian-American identity – the fastest-growing demographic group but also one that faces a huge amount of discrimination amid the country’s racial and ethnic divisions.</p>
<p>For the cover, a black and white photo taken by Asian-American photographer Tommy Kha was painstakingly transformed into a puzzle-like collage by artist Kensuke Koike – perfectly illustrating the subject matter in a way that all great magazine covers do.</p>
